search:Advanced Error Handling in React-.content:
- Ensure Firebase SDK is up to date using `npm install @react-native-firebase/app@latest`
- For iOS, ensure correct bundle ID and signing configuration in Xcode.
- Use `firebase.auth().signInWithEmailAndPassword(email, password)` for email/password authentication.
- Handle errors with try-catch blocks around authentication calls:
  ```javascript
  try {
    const userCredential = await firebase.auth().signInWithEmailAndPassword(email, password);
  } catch (error) {
    console.error('Authentication failed:', error.message);
  }
  ```
- For Apple Sign-In, use `@invertase/react-native-apple-authentication` and ensure correct setup in Firebase.
- Check Firebase project settings for allowed authentication methods.
- Ensure all necessary permissions are granted in the app's Info.plist file for iOS.
